retical perspectives and comparison with Ancient Near Eastern and Greco-Roman literature, Women in Drag shines new light on three strong female characters from the Hebrew Bible and the early days of Jewish literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aWomen in the Bible. 4aAncient. 4aGeneral. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060675140uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146323942840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463239428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463239428/original  a978-3-11-060675-1  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK